<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>
<p>
Let \(V\) be a vector space over a field \(\mathbf F\)
(which is either \(\mathbf R\) or \(\mathbf C\))
and let \(T\in\End(V)\).
</p>
<p>
A scalar \(\lambda\in\mathbf F\) is called an <b>eigenvalue</b>
of \(T\) if
\[T - \lambda\,\id_V\]
is not injective.
</p>
</body>
</html>
